The array elements are accessed using the index. To access array element at index N.
The array starts at index 0, This means the first element has index 0, the second element has index 1 and the nth element has upto.
$ echo ${array_name[N]}
  echo ${distros[2]}

To access all array elements at once.
$ echo ${array_name[*]}
  echo ${distros[*]}

The length of elements.
$ echo ${#array_name[@]}
  echo ${#distros[@]}

To add array elements.
$ array_name+=("new_value")
  distros+=(void)

$ array_name[N]=new_value
  distros[7]=Slackware                                                  7th position (index 6)
  distros[2]=Debian                                                     3rd position (index 2)

To delete an array element.
$ unset array_name[N]
  unset distros[3]

$ unset array_name
  unset distros
